data.text:
Magasin du Nord, Copenhagen, Denmark

Latitude and longitude coordinates are: 55.679207, 12.583428.

Magasin is a Danish department store chain founded by Theodor Wessel and Emil Vett in 1868. Its flagship store, Magasin du Nord, can be found at Kongens Nytorv 13 in Copenhagen, Denmark. It has three other stores in the city, located in the towns of Lyngby and RÃ¸dovre, and in the Field's shopping center. Magasin du Nord was acquired by Peek & Cloppenburg in May 2021. Magasin du Nord on Kongens Nytorv serves as a large shopping center and is home to a number of shops selling fashion brands, jewelry, and home goods as well as a few places to eat.
